The paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques, specifically tiered graph autoencoders and graph classification, for molecular graphs. The focus is on learning latent representations and spaces for molecular graphs, which is a common topic in machine learning and deep learning research (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of graph embeddings and pooling techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of unsupervised learning (tiered graph autoencoders) and supervised learning (graph classification), which are both common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) research.
